I think most of the smartphone these days have reasonably similar battery life. It's a great phone and presumably the best one the market can offer, and here are some tips to enhance the battery life: 
1. Charge the battery fully before using it and use it fully before recharging it (I know it has Li-Ion battery, but remember that even this type of batteries have a finite life and that's unfortunately the truth!!!); 
2. Turn the blue-tooth and Wifi/data off when you don't need it; 
3. don't install unnecessary applications because they can have memory leaks; 
4. Use the push/pull of emails only when needed.
 
This is the best phone (yes, I say it again and again, that it's the best phone the market has to offer) and it needs some respect too. 
 
Only thing I do not like about the phone is the power button on the side. I guess it would be great if Samsung put it by the head :).
 
Cheers.
 
